<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-1073] Error when handling a TIFF image</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1073</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is an error in a TIFF image within a PDF document and when PDCcitt.getRGBImage() is called, there is a disparity between current PDFBox and v0.8.0. The issue is that there now TIFF decoding features whereas the older PDFBox used to hand that off to java.imageio. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug here isn&apos;t in the Ccitt decoder, but rather in how PDCcitt.getRGBImage() handles an error. Rather than bombing out, I have reimplemented the old feature when an error is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 11/04</environment>
        <key id="12514771">PDFBOX-1073</key>
            <summary>Error when handling a TIFF image</summary>
